Altum Health, a division of the University Health Network (UHN), has over 200 dedicated team members committed to providing quality health care & medical services. All our services are founded on principles of early intervention, integrated care delivery and elimination of unnecessary care. Our experts deliver clear and objective recommendations for employers & insurers, proven to address and improve our customers' financial health, workplace reintegration and sustained productivity. Our programs have met the rigorous maximum credentialing standards of the Commission on Accreditation of Rehabilitation Facilities (CARF).

Altum Health, formerly known UHN Rehabilitation Solutions, was established in 1989 to provide expert assessment services within the WSIB Regional Evaluation Centre. Altum Health has delivered health care services to injured workers, as well as those injured in automobile accidents, and those with disability claims across Ontario. Altum Health reinvests all of its profits into the public health care system to support health care services & research.

Altum Health is led and managed by a group of seasoned health care and management professionals including an expert group of physician specialists who are recognized as leaders in their fields.

Our people are key to everything we do at Altum Health. We’re always looking for people to work with us who are aligned with our vision and mission, enjoy working in cross functional teams and really want to make a difference in the lives of our clients.
